spans.text: The only Tribute pitying Love can pay
Desire , or calm fierce Passion's Rage
Relief to offer , if I can't relieve ; Near thy sick Couch with fond Concern to attend , And reach out Cordials to my Dying Friend
Poor hapless Youth ! what Words can ease thy Pain , When Reason
stem the Force of blind Affection's Tide
From careless Sloth thy dull Existence flows , And feeds the Fountain whence itself
the Promise of the future Man
her Shrine the lowly Suppliant laid
her Almighty Breath his Doom receives
his Fate , " Heaven in her Love , Damnation in her Hate
my humble Prayer , " Spare thy poor Servant — OH in Mercy spare
My Joy , my Life , my Final Bliss in Thee
the Creature , " What bold Wretch replies
He tears , and casts the bleeding Orb away
